---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Belgium Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/belgium/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Netherlands for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/netherlands' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'belgiumFit', header: 'Belgium Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€320-460/mo', belgiumFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€380-540/mo', belgiumFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€290-420/mo', belgiumFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€270-400/mo', belgiumFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Belgian Mutuelle', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '€100-150/mo', belgiumFit: 'Mandatory' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€290-460', annual: '€3,480-5,520' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€400-620', annual: '€4,800-7,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€540-820', annual: '€6,480-9,840' },
  { category: 'Belgian Mutuelle (Mandatory)', monthly: '€100-150', annual: '€1,200-1,800' },
  { category: 'Belgian Private Top-up', monthly: '€50-200', annual: '€600-2,400' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Belgium 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Belgium. Belgian mutuelle system, Brussels expat community, visa options, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Belgium"
  subheadline="Belgium offers excellent healthcare, central European location, and multilingual culture—with a strong social security system for residents."
  heroImage="/images/countries/belgium-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Belgium</h2>
  <p>
    Belgium sits at the heart of Europe, offering excellent healthcare, multilingual culture (French, Dutch, German), and easy access to neighboring countries. Brussels hosts EU institutions and has a large international community, making it very expat-friendly.
  </p>

  <p>
    Brussels offers cosmopolitan living with world-class hospitals. Bruges and Ghent in Flanders provide historic charm. Liège and Namur in Wallonia offer French-speaking alternatives. Antwerp combines culture, port history, and good healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; comprehensive social security system</li>
      <li><strong>Languages:</strong> Dutch (Flanders), French (Wallonia), German (small area)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,200-3,500/month; Brussels most expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mild, wet; similar to UK weather</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> EU headquarters; full Schengen member</li>
      <li><strong>Transport:</strong> Excellent trains; central to Europe</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Belgium's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Belgium has mandatory health insurance through mutuelles (sickness funds). The system reimburses 75% of medical costs on average, with patients paying the difference. Quality is excellent, with well-equipped hospitals and specialists.
  </p>

  <p>
    Prescription drugs are heavily subsidized. Hospital care is high quality. Most doctors speak multiple languages, especially in Brussels. The system combines public funding with private delivery, similar to Germany.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Out-of-Pocket Costs</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Belgian healthcare requires co-payments. Standard reimbursement is ~75%, meaning you pay ~25% out of pocket. For hospitalization, daily charges apply (€15-45/day). Many residents add hospitalization insurance to cover these gaps.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Belgium offers pathways for non-EU retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Stay Visa (D Visa)</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with sufficient income (typically €1,500+/month) and comprehensive health insurance. Apply at Belgian embassy, then register in Belgium. Valid 1 year, renewable.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have Belgian citizen or resident family members, family reunification provides a pathway with fewer financial requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement rights. Register with commune after 3 months. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health insurance. Join Belgian mutuelle system.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Belgium requires all residents to have health insurance:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive coverage required</li>
    <li><strong>After registration:</strong> Must join a Belgian mutuelle (sickness fund)</li>
    <li><strong>Mutuelles:</strong> Choose from Christian, Socialist, Liberal, Neutral, or Free mutuelles</li>
    <li><strong>Optional:</strong> Hospitalization insurance for remaining costs</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Belgium</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Start with international insurance for visa application. Once resident, join a Belgian mutuelle (mandatory). Many add hospitalization insurance for private rooms and uncovered costs. Keep international coverage for travel and home country visits.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors moving to Belgium, these providers offer strong European coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Belgium</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Benelux network, direct billing</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> German parent, excellent DACH/Benelux coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Belgian Mutuelle:</strong> Mandatory once resident; affordable</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Belgium.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Belgium combine mandatory and optional elements:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Join mutuelle promptly:</strong> Belgian system is cheaper than international-only</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital insurance:</strong> Add for €50-100/month to cover room and extras</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> €2,000+ excess reduces international premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Belgium exclusion:</strong> Once in mutuelle, exclude Belgium from international policy</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American EU Official, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring in Brussels after EU career. Has Belgian residence. €3,000/month pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Join Partena mutuelle. Add DKV hospitalization insurance. Cigna Global for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Mutuelle ~€120/month + DKV ~€80/month + Cigna ~€300/month (Belgium excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, moving to Bruges. £2,500/month combined pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for visa. Join Belgian mutuelle after registration. Keep BUPA for UK coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€1,000/month combined. After: mutuelle ~€250 + reduced BUPA ~€500/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Dutch Citizen, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EU citizen moving from Amsterdam to Antwerp. Dutch pension €1,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Transfer registration, join Belgian mutuelle. Similar system to Netherlands.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Mutuelle ~€130/month. Much simpler than Dutch basisverzekering system.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which language region is best for English speakers?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Brussels is officially bilingual and very international—English is widely used. Flanders (Dutch-speaking) has good English proficiency. Wallonia (French-speaking) has less English outside Brussels. Most healthcare providers in Brussels speak English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the difference between mutuelles?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        All mutuelles provide the same mandatory reimbursements. Differences are in optional services, hospitalization insurance offerings, and philosophical affiliation (Christian, Socialist, Liberal, etc.). Partena is the largest independent/neutral option.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good are Belgian hospitals?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent. University hospitals in Brussels, Leuven, Ghent, and Liège are world-class. Equipment is modern, specialists well-trained. Wait times are shorter than UK or Canada. The main complaint is co-payment costs, which hospitalization insurance addresses.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Belgium expensive for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate by Western European standards. Brussels is expensive for housing; Wallonia and smaller Flemish cities are more affordable. Healthcare costs are manageable with proper insurance. Food, utilities, and transport are reasonable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Belgium.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Belgian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
